{
  "text": "Understanding the difference between public and private subnets is crucial. Public subnets have a direct route to the Internet through an Internet gateway. Instances here get public IP addresses and can be accessed from the Internet. This is perfect for load balancers and bastion hosts. Private subnets have no direct Internet route. Instances here only have private IP addresses and cannot be reached from the Internet. This is where you place databases, application servers, and sensitive workloads. However, private subnets can act as a gateway to all areas.",
